column5: Has anyone been down to St Williams for perch lately, I want to take my co worker and her daughter perch fishing and I am not sure weather to take them there or Lake Simcoe?  Any help would be appreciated.  Darren
There is plenty of ice at St. Williams and plenty of fish being caught.  http://www.longpoint.on.ca/forum/index.php?forums/fishing-reports/

Buddy called me, he brought home 35 Monday said he must have caught over 100 to get 35 keepers.2 operators renting huts there, $50.00 per adult 40 for kids. Get there early for a parking spot below the hill.
Heard it was real slow Sunday. Better Monday, apparently. Might just give er a go soon myself.
